pageContext.claim: “I won the Senate, and that's historic too, because if you look at presidents in the White House it's almost never happened where you won a seat. We won -- we now have 53 as opposed to 51 and we have 53 great Senators in the U.S. Senate. We won. That's a tremendous victory. Nobody talks about that.”
pageContext.analysis: There was extensive coverage of the Senate races. There is little historic about a one-seat gain in the Senate; Republicans had started the session with 52 seats. In fact, given that mostly Democratic seats were up for reelection, in many red seats, the outcome was not unexpected.
